1 A RESOLUTION encouraging Kentucky policymakers to study, develop, and
2 implement economic development policies to incentivize biopharmaceutical investment
3 and innovation in Kentucky.
4 WHEREAS, the Commonwealth has made significant investments in
5 pharmaceutical research in recent years, both through recurring general fund
6 commitments and consequential, one-time expenditures into projects like the LifeSciKY,
7 a lab incubator accelerating science, entrepreneurship, education, and economic
8 development; and
9 WHEREAS, biopharmaceutical investment and innovation is a major economic
10 driver, with the potential to bring many high-paying jobs to the Commonwealth; and
11 WHEREAS, each phase of the biopharmaceutical innovation process requires
12 immense amounts of brainpower and capital, and inventors and investors look to mitigate
13 their risk by moving to locations that provide better investment incentives; and
14 WHEREAS, the state of Indiana recently announced a $1 billion commitment in the
15 form of tax credits to attract major biopharmaceutical companies to their state, with the
16 goal of creating 100,000 new high-wage jobs over the next 10 years; and
17 WHEREAS, the Commonwealth is home to many talented minds that, without the
18 proper incentives, may move elsewhere to invest and develop these types of life-changing
19 innovations; and
20 WHEREAS, the Commonwealth would benefit greatly by implementing policies
21 that strengthen biopharmaceutical investment and innovation and would attract and keep
22 these important developments in the Commonwealth;
23 NOW, THEREFORE,
24 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
25 Kentucky:
26 Section 1. The Senate hereby encourages Kentucky policymakers to study,
27 develop, and implement economic development policies to incentivize biopharmaceutical
Page 1 of 2
