UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2587
1 investment and innovation in the Commonwealth, including but not limited to:
2 (1) The creation of tax credits, grants, or similar incentive mechanisms that
3 meaningfully support research and development investments by both commercial stage
4 entities and pre-revenue and early-stage biopharmaceutical companies;
5 (2) The establishment of graduated incentive tiers that provide enhanced benefits
6 for companies that are headquartered in the Commonwealth, or relocate their principal
7 place of business to the Commonwealth, in recognition that biopharmaceutical
8 investment generates high-quality jobs beyond research and development, including but
9 not limited to finance, accounting, legal, regulatory, business development, human
10 resources, manufacturing, and executive leadership roles, and that incentive structures
11 should encourage the full corporate and operational footprint of these companies to reside
12 in Kentucky;
13 (3) The development of a dedicated and reliable funding pool, to support such
14 incentives and to ensure the Commonwealth remains competitive with peer states making
15 substantially larger commitments to attract life sciences investments, including existing
16 incentive programs in other sectors of the Commonwealth that exceed this level of annual
17 funding; and
18 (4) The alignment of any such incentive program with the Commonwealth's
19 existing investments in life sciences infrastructure, workforce development, and research
20 commercialization, so as to maximize return on investment, retain homegrown
21 innovation, and attract external capital to the Commonwealth.
22 Section 2. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
23 Resolution to Senator Shelley Funke Frommeyer for distribution.
